Start the Kubernetes cluster:
minikube start --driver=docker
minikube status
kubectl get nodes

Create the nginx pod using YAML:
notepad nginx-pod.yaml

Paste the following in the file:
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
name: nginx-pod
labels:
app: nginx
spec:
containers:

name: nginx
image: nginx:latest
ports:

containerPort: 80

Apply the YAML and verify the pod:
kubectl apply -f nginx-pod.yaml
kubectl get pods
kubectl describe pod nginx-pod

Access the pod in browser using port-forward:
kubectl port-forward pod/nginx-pod 8080:80
Open browser at: http://localhost:8080

Stop port-forward using Ctrl + C

Delete the pod:
kubectl delete pod nginx-pod

Create a deployment:
kubectl create deployment my-nginx --image=nginx
kubectl get deployments
kubectl get pods -l app=my-nginx

Scale the deployment to 3 replicas:
kubectl scale deployment my-nginx --replicas=3
kubectl get pods

Perform a rolling update:
kubectl set image deployment/my-nginx nginx=nginx:1.25
kubectl rollout status deployment/my-nginx

Rollback the deployment if required:
kubectl rollout undo deployment/my-nginx

Expose the deployment as a NodePort service:
kubectl expose deployment my-nginx --type=NodePort --port=80
kubectl get svc
minikube service my-nginx --url
Open the displayed URL in your browser to see the Nginx page.

Cleanup all resources:
kubectl delete svc my-nginx
kubectl delete deployment my-nginx
kubectl delete all --all -n default

Stop and delete the Minikube cluster:
minikube stop
minikube delete
